translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah drew out the magical energies from deep within her."
    new "Sarah drew out the magical energies from deep within her."

    old "With a primal scream, she released all the build of magical energy in a single burst."
    new "With a primal scream, she released all the build of magical energy in a single burst."

    old "She felt the tentacles withdraw from her body."
    new "She felt the tentacles withdraw from her body."

    old "All about her, the screeching sounds of the tortured spirits, suffering her magical burns."
    new "All about her, the screeching sounds of the tortured spirits, suffering her magical burns."

    old "And around her, the void began to recede."
    new "And around her, the void began to recede."

    old "Slowly, Sarah felt the world come back into form."
    new "Slowly, Sarah felt the world come back into form."

    old "The scar in reality remained, but was pushed back to what it had been before."
    new "The scar in reality remained, but was pushed back to what it had been before."

    old "The ruined room, still as it was."
    new "The ruined room, still as it was."

    old "She had not moved at all."
    new "She had not moved at all."

    old "Before her, the unnatural flaw in reality continued to linger."
    new "Before her, the unnatural flaw in reality continued to linger."

    old "Something about it, so profoundly upsetting to her."
    new "Something about it, so profoundly upsetting to her."

    old "She finally brought herself to turn away from it."
    new "She finally brought herself to turn away from it."

    old "As she turned, Sarah saw the stones in the ruin begin to shake."
    new "As she turned, Sarah saw the stones in the ruin begin to shake."

    old "For a moment, she feared another earthquake, then as one, the rocks scattered in every direction."
    new "For a moment, she feared another earthquake, then as one, the rocks scattered in every direction."

    old "Sarah raised her hands, suspecting the creature might have survived."
    new "Sarah raised her hands, suspecting the creature might have survived."

    old "Then she lowered them again, seeing who it was."
    new "Then she lowered them again, seeing who it was."

    old "Hecate, holding up a magical barrier, had shielded herself and the others from the falling rocks."
    new "Hecate, holding up a magical barrier, had shielded herself and the others from the falling rocks."

    old "Sarah's heart began to race."
    new "Sarah's heart began to race."

    old "She rushed across the ruined stone, stumbling and tripping."
    new "She rushed across the ruined stone, stumbling and tripping."

    old "She threw her arms around the girl, nearly lifting he off the ground."
    new "She threw her arms around the girl, nearly lifting he off the ground."

    old "You're safe!"
    new "You're safe!"

    old "Sarah hugged the girl so tight, she could feel her bones."
    new "Sarah hugged the girl so tight, she could feel her bones."

    old "Relief rushed over her."
    new "Relief rushed over her."

    old "Are you hurt?"
    new "Are you hurt?"

    old "I'm fine, don't worry. The barrier protected me."
    new "I'm fine, don't worry. The barrier protected me."

    old "Sarah saw Hecate look at her from the corner of her eyes."
    new "Sarah saw Hecate look at her from the corner of her eyes."

    old "We're fine too, thanks for asking."
    new "We're fine too, thanks for asking."

    old "But Sarah had no care for anyone else. Her friend was alive, and that was all that mattered."
    new "But Sarah had no care for anyone else. Her friend was alive, and that was all that mattered."

    old "It got close for a minute, but we're unharmed mostly."
    new "It got close for a minute, but we're unharmed mostly."

    old "The creature gave you a real beating, and after that it turned back on us."
    new "The creature gave you a real beating, and after that it turned back on us."

    old "The floor didn't last much longer. All that magic, and the creature's strength, it's a miracle it lasted as long as it did."
    new "The floor didn't last much longer. All that magic, and the creature's strength, it's a miracle it lasted as long as it did."

    old "And the creature?"
    new "And the creature?"

    old "Dead, or currently dying."
    new "Dead, or currently dying."

    old "It got trapped underneath all the falling rocks."
    new "It got trapped underneath all the falling rocks."

    old "Unlike us, the thing didn't have a skilled witch to produce a barrier."
    new "Unlike us, the thing didn't have a skilled witch to produce a barrier."

    old "Ah, skilled am I now? A rare compliment from my man-servant."
    new "Ah, skilled am I now? A rare compliment from my man-servant."

    old "Gabriel rolled his eyes."
    new "Gabriel rolled his eyes."

    old "Don't get too used to it."
    new "Don't get too used to it."

    old "Hecate looked back at Sarah."
    new "Hecate looked back at Sarah."

    old "You're the real miracle here."
    new "You're the real miracle here."

    old "I was sure that you'd be dead. You were too far for me to protect you."
    new "I was sure that you'd be dead. You were too far for me to protect you."

    old "Guess I just got lucky."
    new "Guess I just got lucky."

    old "Really lucky..."
    new "Really lucky..."

    old "Hecate's voice trailed off as if she didn't quite believe it."
    new "Hecate's voice trailed off as if she didn't quite believe it."

    old "Was it hard though, to maintain the barrier for all that time?"
    new "Was it hard though, to maintain the barrier for all that time?"

    old "Hecate frowned."
    new "Hecate frowned."

    old "Time?"
    new "Time?"

    old "The roof caved in barely a minute ago."
    new "The roof caved in barely a minute ago."

    old "A minute...Sarah wondered. Was that really possible?"
    new "A minute...Sarah wondered. Was that really possible?"

    old "She was certain more time had passed. Or did the void warp both reality and time?"
    new "She was certain more time had passed. Or did the void warp both reality and time?"

    old "Hecate looked past her."
    new "Hecate looked past her."

    old "She pointed."
    new "She pointed."

    old "Well, that's what we came here to find I suppose."
    new "Well, that's what we came here to find I suppose."

    old "Sarah looked at the scar, still lingering in the air. Alien."
    new "Sarah looked at the scar, still lingering in the air. Alien."

    old "Did you go near it?"
    new "Did you go near it?"

    old "Only for a moment."
    new "Only for a moment."

    old "Good. Best you don't touch it directly. Or get too close."
    new "Good. Best you don't touch it directly. Or get too close."

    old "Gabriel walked forward, studying the anomaly."
    new "Gabriel walked forward, studying the anomaly."

    old "It's as you feared, Hecate."
    new "It's as you feared, Hecate."

    old "These are called Voidrifts. They're wounds upon reality."
    new "These are called Voidrifts. They're wounds upon reality."

    old "Wounds?"
    new "Wounds?"

    old "Yes. Their reality and ours lay atop one another, with only a thin layer between them."
    new "Yes. Their reality and ours lay atop one another, with only a thin layer between them."

    old "These things represent the ripping of that fabric."
    new "These things represent the ripping of that fabric."

    old "A product of the endless scratching claws of our enemy."
    new "A product of the endless scratching claws of our enemy."

    old "You've seen one before?"
    new "You've seen one before?"

    old "No. I don't even anyone has seen one for centuries. Millenia, maybe."
    new "No. I don't even anyone has seen one for centuries. Millenia, maybe."

    old "But the drawings in the Citadel...they are clear enough. No mistake about it."
    new "But the drawings in the Citadel...they are clear enough. No mistake about it."

    old "So this...is like a gateway to their world?"
    new "So this...is like a gateway to their world?"

    old "More like a gateway into ours."
    new "More like a gateway into ours."

    old "Hecate turned to Gabriel."
    new "Hecate turned to Gabriel."

    old "We will have to return to the Citadel. Inform the Order."
    new "We will have to return to the Citadel. Inform the Order."

    old "Gabriel only nodded."
    new "Gabriel only nodded."

    old "What do we do about it?"
    new "What do we do about it?"

    old "The veil between our world and theirs is far beyond our power to affect."
    new "The veil between our world and theirs is far beyond our power to affect."

    old "The injury will only grow."
    new "The injury will only grow."

    old "You mean this rift will expand?"
    new "You mean this rift will expand?"

    old "And more will form."
    new "And more will form."

    old "Soon...our enemy will be upon us."
    new "Soon...our enemy will be upon us."

    old "You must warn Xan, should you see him."
    new "You must warn Xan, should you see him."

    old "I will warn the others in the Order. It will be up to them to decide what to do next."
    new "I will warn the others in the Order. It will be up to them to decide what to do next."

    old "Sarah saw real worry on Hecate's face for the first time."
    new "Sarah saw real worry on Hecate's face for the first time."

    old "How long do we have? Before they attack?"
    new "How long do we have? Before they attack?"

    old "Hecate didn't move, only looking at the thing."
    new "Hecate didn't move, only looking at the thing."

    old "Months. Years. I don't know. All I know is that they will come."
    new "Months. Years. I don't know. All I know is that they will come."

    old "Still, first things first. We need to get out of this place."
    new "Still, first things first. We need to get out of this place."

    old "I want to see clear sky again."
    new "I want to see clear sky again."

    old "Sarah nodded. She wanted much the same."
    new "Sarah nodded. She wanted much the same."

    old "Together, the two mages began to burn away at the rocks."
    new "Together, the two mages began to burn away at the rocks."

    old "Samayra helped as well, though her magics were far weaker than either of the other two."
    new "Samayra helped as well, though her magics were far weaker than either of the other two."

    old "Their magical fires cut at the stone, blasting and cutting at the stone, slowly carving a way out."
    new "Their magical fires cut at the stone, blasting and cutting at the stone, slowly carving a way out."

    old "When the ceiling had collapsed, it had brought down so much stone on them, it was hard to fathom."
    new "When the ceiling had collapsed, it had brought down so much stone on them, it was hard to fathom."

    old "Now, as they were cutting their way out again, they slowly took stock of it all."
    new "Now, as they were cutting their way out again, they slowly took stock of it all."

    old "And each realized just how lucky they were to still be alive."
    new "And each realized just how lucky they were to still be alive."

    old "After hours, with their muscles and energies spend, they finally made their way out of the ruin, back to the entrance."
    new "After hours, with their muscles and energies spend, they finally made their way out of the ruin, back to the entrance."

    old "Hecate looked at Sarah."
    new "Hecate looked at Sarah."

    old "Sarah, me and Gabriel will need to make use of Xan's house."
    new "Sarah, me and Gabriel will need to make use of Xan's house."

    old "We could travel back through the jungle, but it would take weeks."
    new "We could travel back through the jungle, but it would take weeks."

    old "But I also don't know where the entrance to the House is in this place. Can you show me?"
    new "But I also don't know where the entrance to the House is in this place. Can you show me?"

    old "We will need to head back through the old city, cut through the main plaza."
    new "We will need to head back through the old city, cut through the main plaza."

    old "Lead the way."
    new "Lead the way."

    old "Together, they made their way back out of the Imperial Palace."
    new "Together, they made their way back out of the Imperial Palace."

    old "When they stepped out, the sky had already turned dark."
    new "When they stepped out, the sky had already turned dark."

    old "They marched in silence for a while, but Sarah soon realized it would be too far."
    new "They marched in silence for a while, but Sarah soon realized it would be too far."

    old "The effort of blasting through the stone had exhausted them, not to mention the fight with the creature."
    new "The effort of blasting through the stone had exhausted them, not to mention the fight with the creature."

    old "We'll make camp."
    new "We'll make camp."

    old "We can reach the house tomorrow."
    new "We can reach the house tomorrow."

    old "Good idea. Better that we get some rest. We don't want to walk into an Orc trap unprepared."
    new "Good idea. Better that we get some rest. We don't want to walk into an Orc trap unprepared."

    old "This information is too important! We cannot wait!"
    new "This information is too important! We cannot wait!"

    old "Gabriel turned to her."
    new "Gabriel turned to her."

    old "We must wait, exactly because it is so important."
    new "We must wait, exactly because it is so important."

    old "If we die, nobody will know of it. We cannot risk it. One day will make no difference in the outcome of a war."
    new "If we die, nobody will know of it. We cannot risk it. One day will make no difference in the outcome of a war."

    old "Hecate sighed, but surrendered to Gabriel's argument."
    new "Hecate sighed, but surrendered to Gabriel's argument."

    old "Go, get some sleep. I'll keep guard."
    new "Go, get some sleep. I'll keep guard."

    old "Hecate offered no resistance and quickly went to sleep."
    new "Hecate offered no resistance and quickly went to sleep."

    old "Samayra, likewise, was quick to take Gabriel up on the offer of getting some sleep."
    new "Samayra, likewise, was quick to take Gabriel up on the offer of getting some sleep."

    old "Go ahead, get some sleep."
    new "Go ahead, get some sleep."

    old "I'm too awake. I don't think I'd get any rest."
    new "I'm too awake. I don't think I'd get any rest."

    old "Gabriel smiled."
    new "Gabriel smiled."

    old "I'm the same way."
    new "I'm the same way."

    old "Hecy always thinks I'm some kind of stoic Knight. The truth is I'm just a terrible sleeper."
    new "Hecy always thinks I'm some kind of stoic Knight. The truth is I'm just a terrible sleeper."

    old "Hecy?"
    new "Hecy?"

    old "Gabriel looked flustered."
    new "Gabriel looked flustered."

    old "Sorry, Hecate."
    new "Sorry, Hecate."

    old "I didn't know the two of you had nicknames for each other."
    new "I didn't know the two of you had nicknames for each other."

    old "It was different when I was first assigned to her."
    new "It was different when I was first assigned to her."

    old "But she's so informal...it has a way of getting under your skin."
    new "But she's so informal...it has a way of getting under your skin."

    old "A lifetime of protocol and proper decorum, all forgotten after just a few years with her."
    new "A lifetime of protocol and proper decorum, all forgotten after just a few years with her."

    old "Sarah gestured from him to her."
    new "Sarah gestured from him to her."

    old "Are the two of you..."
    new "Are the two of you..."

    old "She left the implication up in the air."
    new "She left the implication up in the air."

    old "He paused for a long time before answering."
    new "He paused for a long time before answering."

    old "It's complicated."
    new "It's complicated."

    old "It often is."
    new "It often is."

    old "They sat near the edge of the campfire, keeping watch over the the ruined city."
    new "They sat near the edge of the campfire, keeping watch over the the ruined city."

    old "If there were Orcs or Goblins out there, there were no signs of them."
    new "If there were Orcs or Goblins out there, there were no signs of them."

    old "Do you think we'll be safe out here?"
    new "Do you think we'll be safe out here?"

    old "The Orcs and Goblins like easy prey."
    new "The Orcs and Goblins like easy prey."

    old "By now they must have told each other that there are mages around."
    new "By now they must have told each other that there are mages around."

    old "They won't try anything."
    new "They won't try anything."

    old "Still, better to be safe."
    new "Still, better to be safe."

    old "Sarah looked out across the empty plaza."
    new "Sarah looked out across the empty plaza."

    old "And the voidrift?"
    new "And the voidrift?"

    old "Gabriel sighed."
    new "Gabriel sighed."

    old "I don't know as much about that as Hecate, but...if she's afraid, then I'm afraid."
    new "I don't know as much about that as Hecate, but...if she's afraid, then I'm afraid."

    old "Ever since we started travelling here, she's been worried."
    new "Ever since we started travelling here, she's been worried."

    old "And she usually doesn't scare easily."
    new "And she usually doesn't scare easily."

    old "Sarah and Gabriel each went quiet."
    new "Sarah and Gabriel each went quiet."

    old "They kept their watch, but for the rest of the night, no attack came."
    new "They kept their watch, but for the rest of the night, no attack came."

    old "The next morning, they set out early and kept a steady march."
    new "The next morning, they set out early and kept a steady march."

    old "Crossing back across the ruined city, Sarah soon managed to guide them to the entrance that lead to the House."
    new "Crossing back across the ruined city, Sarah soon managed to guide them to the entrance that lead to the House."

    old "As they stepped through the hidden doorway, they arrived back home."
    new "As they stepped through the hidden doorway, they arrived back home."

    old "If you see Xan again, tell him of what we saw."
    new "If you see Xan again, tell him of what we saw."

    old "I'll travel back to the Citadel and warn the Order. After that..."
    new "I'll travel back to the Citadel and warn the Order. After that..."

    old "We'll, let's wait for their verdict first."
    new "We'll, let's wait for their verdict first."

    old "Just like that, the Witch and the Knight stepped back out through another doorway, taking them to where they wanted to go."
    new "Just like that, the Witch and the Knight stepped back out through another doorway, taking them to where they wanted to go."

    old "Save for Samayra, the house was emtpy again."
    new "Save for Samayra, the house was emtpy again."

    old "The house was empty again."
    new "The house was empty again."

    old "Suddenly, with everything now behind her, Sarah felt just how tired she really was."
    new "Suddenly, with everything now behind her, Sarah felt just how tired she really was."

    old "The pain in her muscles, the exhaustion in her mind."
    new "The pain in her muscles, the exhaustion in her mind."

    old "She fell back into the chair behind her desk."
    new "She fell back into the chair behind her desk."

    old "Samayra stood on the other side of the desk."
    new "Samayra stood on the other side of the desk."

    old "I mean...helping out. I hope I wasn't too much of a burden."
    new "I mean...helping out. I hope I wasn't too much of a burden."

    old "Not at all. I was happy you were there."
    new "Not at all. I was happy you were there."

    old "It's just...we finally have a moment of peace and I'm trying to process it all."
    new "It's just...we finally have a moment of peace and I'm trying to process it all."

    old "My problem?"
    new "My problem?"

    old "Yeah, you always try to figure everything out. Sometimes you just have to let them settle."
    new "Yeah, you always try to figure everything out. Sometimes you just have to let them settle."

    old "And how do you propose I do that?"
    new "And how do you propose I do that?"

    old "Samayra gave a wide smile."
    new "Samayra gave a wide smile."

    old "Easy!"
    new "Easy!"

    old "We both earned a day of rest. I say we use it!"
    new "We both earned a day of rest. I say we use it!"

    old "Just tell me what you want to do and we'll do it."
    new "Just tell me what you want to do and we'll do it."

    old "If it was true that she had earned a day of rest, then she had to admit she was eager to use it."
    new "If it was true that she had earned a day of rest, then she had to admit she was eager to use it."

    old "Closing her eyes, she replayed all the events in her mind."
    new "Closing her eyes, she replayed all the events in her mind."

    old "What to do about it all...she wasn't too certain."
    new "What to do about it all...she wasn't too certain."

    old "She had earned a day of rest, and she was eager to take it."
    new "She had earned a day of rest, and she was eager to take it."

    old "A pensive expression came on Samayra's face for a moment."
    new "A pensive expression came on Samayra's face for a moment."

    old "How about..."
    new "How about..."

    old "The park?"
    new "The park?"

    old "Sarah looked out of the window. It looked like a beautiful day."
    new "Sarah looked out of the window. It looked like a beautiful day."

    old "Sure, let's get out of the house."
    new "Sure, let's get out of the house."

    old "It seemed about as good an idea as any to her."
    new "It seemed about as good an idea as any to her."

    old "The two of them stepped out of the house, letting the door fall shut behind them."
    new "The two of them stepped out of the house, letting the door fall shut behind them."

    old "Instantly, the warm sunlight greeted them."
    new "Instantly, the warm sunlight greeted them."

    old "They took a quick turn, heading towards the main street of Lethram."
    new "They took a quick turn, heading towards the main street of Lethram."

    old "The main street ran through the center of the city. Outside of the docks, it was one of the most populated parts of Lethram."
    new "The main street ran through the center of the city. Outside of the docks, it was one of the most populated parts of Lethram."

    old "Sarah walked along Samayra."
    new "Sarah walked along Samayra."

    old "Her own mind was still concerned with the events of the days prior. Samayra seemed less weighed down."
    new "Her own mind was still concerned with the events of the days prior. Samayra seemed less weighed down."

    old "You're happy."
    new "You're happy."

    old "Samayra turned around, smiling."
    new "Samayra turned around, smiling."

    old "What's not to be happy about?"
    new "What's not to be happy about?"

    old "For Samayra, being happy seemed to be her emotional baseline."
    new "For Samayra, being happy seemed to be her emotional baseline."

    old "Sometimes Sarah found herself jealous of how weightlessly the girl walked through life. How easily she seemed to let things fall from her shoulders."
    new "Sometimes Sarah found herself jealous of how weightlessly the girl walked through life. How easily she seemed to let things fall from her shoulders."

    old "She had her own fair share of trauma, but she never showed it."
    new "She had her own fair share of trauma, but she never showed it."

    old "Here, we can go through here."
    new "Here, we can go through here."

    old "Samayra pointed towards one of the side streets."
    new "Samayra pointed towards one of the side streets."

    old "Sarah just nodded and followed Samayra."
    new "Sarah just nodded and followed Samayra."

    old "It's actually a shortcut...I think..."
    new "It's actually a shortcut...I think..."

    old "When she had brought Samayra to Lethram, Sarah had initially been constantly worried about her."
    new "When she had brought Samayra to Lethram, Sarah had initially been constantly worried about her."

    old "Worried if she'd find her place, if she wasn't too sad, too lonely."
    new "Worried if she'd find her place, if she wasn't too sad, too lonely."

    old "Instead, Samayra had kept surprising her."
    new "Instead, Samayra had kept surprising her."

    old "By now, the girl knew the city almost as well as Sarah did, and at times, even better."
    new "By now, the girl knew the city almost as well as Sarah did, and at times, even better."

    old "Sarah realized just how locked up in Xan's house she had been all these years."
    new "Sarah realized just how locked up in Xan's house she had been all these years."

    old "How little she knew of the city that had now become her home."
    new "How little she knew of the city that had now become her home."

    old "Watching Samayra happily bounce along the cobblestones, Sarah envied her more."
    new "Watching Samayra happily bounce along the cobblestones, Sarah envied her more."

    old "Finally, after following the twisting roads, they finally ended up in the main park."
    new "Finally, after following the twisting roads, they finally ended up in the main park."

    old "Lethram was a rich city, and as such it was home to more than a few parks, but none as impressive as this one."
    new "Lethram was a rich city, and as such it was home to more than a few parks, but none as impressive as this one."

    old "Walking along the paved path, Sarah noticed the many different people that gathered here."
    new "Walking along the paved path, Sarah noticed the many different people that gathered here."

    old "Lethram was quite different from where she had grown up."
    new "Lethram was quite different from where she had grown up."

    old "In Rosanna, most everyone was either a Noble or a Serf."
    new "In Rosanna, most everyone was either a Noble or a Serf."

    old "Sure, some of the Serfs worked more complicated jobs, like blacksmiths, but most of them were simple farmers."
    new "Sure, some of the Serfs worked more complicated jobs, like blacksmiths, but most of them were simple farmers."

    old "The odd merchant might be lucky and earn enough money to be rich, but they'd still never be a Noble."
    new "The odd merchant might be lucky and earn enough money to be rich, but they'd still never be a Noble."

    old "Here in Lethram, things were quite different."
    new "Here in Lethram, things were quite different."

    old "Titles and such seemed to be much less prevalant here."
    new "Titles and such seemed to be much less prevalant here."

    old "Instead, the people belonged to several large Guilds that each covered a part of the city's many needs."
    new "Instead, the people belonged to several large Guilds that each covered a part of the city's many needs."

    old "The Building Guild. The Merchant Guild. And most importantly, the Shipping Guild."
    new "The Building Guild. The Merchant Guild. And most importantly, the Shipping Guild."

    old "Here in Lethram, a person saw themselves by their Guild association, more than anything else."
    new "Here in Lethram, a person saw themselves by their Guild association, more than anything else."

    old "And unlike in Rosanna, where Merchants were often looked on with suspicion, here in Lethram, Merchants were considered an honorable trade."
    new "And unlike in Rosanna, where Merchants were often looked on with suspicion, here in Lethram, Merchants were considered an honorable trade."

    old "In Rosanna, a person's fate was settled by birth."
    new "In Rosanna, a person's fate was settled by birth."

    old "Here, all the children of the city were given the same education, and only when they reached maturity were they expected to pledge to a Guild."
    new "Here, all the children of the city were given the same education, and only when they reached maturity were they expected to pledge to a Guild."

    old "Anyone could come form anywhere and become anything."
    new "Anyone could come form anywhere and become anything."

    old "Having lived her for so many years, Sarah couldn't help but feel Rosanna's system to have been archaic."
    new "Having lived her for so many years, Sarah couldn't help but feel Rosanna's system to have been archaic."

    old "Then again, after the Fall of Rosanna by the Tribes, she wasn't even sure if there was much of a system left at all."
    new "Then again, after the Fall of Rosanna by the Tribes, she wasn't even sure if there was much of a system left at all."

    old "Who knew how the Tribes ruled their lands."
    new "Who knew how the Tribes ruled their lands."

    old "There's a spot over here, in the grass."
    new "There's a spot over here, in the grass."

